  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The proposed research aims to determine the prevalence, size, shape and histology of flat
      colorectal neoplasms in a cohort of asymptomatic, average-risk individuals presenting for
      screening colonoscopy. Patients will be randomized to either conventional colonoscopy or
      chromocolonoscopy, where the entire colon will be sprayed with indigocarmine dye and examined
      in the usual manner. The primary outcome will be the total number of adenomas detected, with
      special attention to the subgroup of flat and depressed lesions. To promote the
      generalizability of the results, neoplasms will be described according to standard Western
      and Japanese classification schemes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
